    <!-- Hysteresis arrays for smooth brightness transitions
         (Standard AOSP resources, added in Android 12+).
         These prevent flickering when ambient light hovers near
         a threshold boundary. Extracted from stock vendor RRO.

         Verified via aapt2: these arrays are NOT in the build-time
         framework-res (Linux desktop reference). They ARE present in
         Android 12+ AOSP source. On the target A16 QPR2 GSI:
         - If present → works normally (smoother transitions)
         - If absent  → idmap2 silently skips them (no crash, no bootloop)
         This is safe either way. -->
